---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro"
---

<Layout link="about" title="About – Raul Muela Morey">
  <main class="max-w-3xl mx-auto mt-24 px-6 pb-24 flex flex-col items-center">
    <div class="mb-8 text-center">
      <img
        src="images/Avatar.png"
        width="120"
        height="120"
        decoding="async"
        loading="lazy"
        alt="Raul's avatar"
        class="mx-auto w-[120px] rounded-full mb-4 border border-slate-700 shadow-lg shadow-black/40"
      />

      <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.25em] text-slate-400">
        About me
      </p>
      <h1 class="mt-2 text-2xl lg:text-3xl font-bold text-white">
        Hi, I’m <span class="text-[#FACC15]">Raul Muela</span>
      </h1>
    </div>

    <section class="space-y-4 text-base lg:text-lg text-slate-300 text-center lg:text-left">
      <p>
  I'm a self-taught blockchain developer from Mallorca, Spain, with 4 years 
  of experience building DeFi protocols and full-stack dApps.
</p>

<p>
  I started programming five years ago, experimenting with small projects on 
  my own. That curiosity led me to Web3, where I've spent the last few years 
  learning how smart contracts work, designing protocols, and shipping real 
  applications end-to-end.
</p>

<p>
  My two main projects are RWA Exchange — a decentralized exchange for 
  tokenized real-world stocks using Chainlink Functions and the Alpaca 
  broker API — and CrossLink, a cross-chain lending protocol using 
  Chainlink CCIP with oracle-free risk management.
</p>

<p>
  I enjoy working at the intersection of on-chain logic and real-world use 
  cases, writing clean and well-tested code, and understanding how things 
  work under the hood.
</p>

<p class="pt-2 text-sm lg:text-base text-slate-400">
  I'm currently finishing a Higher National Diploma in Web Development at 
  Cesur and looking for a remote role as a blockchain or smart contract 
  developer where I can contribute, keep learning, and help build useful 
  products in the space.
</p>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>
